This new design is available now on my big cartel! Woven cotton blanket, 84x62 inches! 

I made this blanket with the intention of it being a talisman! The symbols are read from the outside to in. The happy skulls are guides, welcoming clownish figures that also hold within them a confrontation of our basest fear, death. From there we have the dagger, a protective tool, a symbol of bravery and ability, a necessary implement as we venture deeper to the realm of the moon. The moon is a powerful ally, and yet it also represents the subconscious, the primordial, deeply hidden aspects of self that make up the majority of our minds yet lay dormant behind the veil of our conscious experience. From there we have the eye, consciousness itself, crying tears of bliss, tears arising from unity consciousness. Then the heart, nothing truly worthy can be accomplished without an open heart. Then a blooming flower which doubles as a star, a symbol of growth, beauty, harmony, and transience. And finally the interior chamber! The checkered ground represents duality consciousness, the illusion of separateness, the background on which human experience is set, the board on which we play this human game. The sun stands above, cosmic energy, positivity, clarity, and source. Death stands center, completing the journey we are reborn, renewed, and victorious over the illusion of life-death. The reaper is also symbolic of purification, elimination of what is not necessary, and the ending of a cycle. And finally there is the snake, representing the unlocking of our Devine power, stillness that can be called into dynamic action, victory of our latent potentials.

I summersault to break the chains of my own making and allow new realities to germinate and bloom!

Here’s something I discovered about myself sorta recently! Which isn’t really a discovery so much as a deepening of an understanding that I already had. Last year, when @twoheadedgirl__ and I did the Camino de Santiago, I was in more physical pain than I’ve ever been, yet I was happier than I had been in years! Ecstatic actually. I discovered that for my particular brand of ADHD I am happiest and most balanced if I’m doing intense physical activity. But like intensssse, like almost masochistic really. This is especially true if I’m doing it with friends, or in some kind of group setting. And the research on this supports my experience, since ADHD is essentially a dopamine deficiency, dumping dopamine, noradrenaline, and serotonin into the system naturally helps it out. And surprise surprise, I feel happier now that I have been in a very long time! Which is wild cause in the middle of the thing, I just wanna die lol.

Two eyes to look, one eye that sees. Yaaaa knoooowwwwww, from the binary, consciousness of separateness, to the singular, unified “all is one” consciousness I love so much.
